PRIVACY POLICY FOR ASHLEY MUSIC BOT
LAST UPDATED: NOVEMBER 2025

1. INTRODUCTION
THIS PRIVACY POLICY EXPLAINS HOW ASHLEY MUSIC BOT (“THE BOT”) COLLECTS, USES, STORES, AND PROTECTS USER INFORMATION. BY USING THE BOT, YOU AGREE TO THE TERMS OUTLINED IN THIS POLICY. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE, PLEASE STOP USING THE BOT IMMEDIATELY.

2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT
ASHLEY MUSIC BOT COLLECTS ONLY THE MINIMUM DATA NECESSARY TO OPERATE EFFECTIVELY:


USER IDS: TO IDENTIFY COMMAND EXECUTION AND USER SETTINGS.


GUILD (SERVER) IDS: TO MANAGE BOT SETTINGS AND CONFIGURATIONS PER SERVER.


CHANNEL IDS AND MESSAGE CONTENT: TEMPORARILY PROCESSED ONLY WHEN A COMMAND IS USED.


PLAYLIST OR QUEUE DATA: STORED LOCALLY OR TEMPORARILY IN CACHE FOR FUNCTIONALITY PURPOSES.


NO SENSITIVE OR PERSONAL INFORMATION (SUCH AS EMAILS, PASSWORDS, OR PAYMENT DETAILS) IS COLLECTED.

3. HOW WE USE THE INFORMATION
THE COLLECTED DATA IS USED EXCLUSIVELY TO:


ENABLE CORE BOT FUNCTIONS SUCH AS MUSIC PLAYBACK AND COMMAND RESPONSE.


MAINTAIN USER AND SERVER PREFERENCES.


IMPROVE PERFORMANCE AND RELIABILITY OF THE SERVICE.


ENSURE ABUSE PREVENTION AND SECURITY WITHIN THE BOT.


THE DATA IS NEVER SOLD, SHARED, OR USED FOR MARKETING PURPOSES.

4. DATA STORAGE AND RETENTION


ALL DATA IS STORED SECURELY IN CONTROLLED ENVIRONMENTS.


ONLY NECESSARY DATA IS RETAINED AS LONG AS REQUIRED FOR FUNCTIONALITY.


WHEN A SERVER REMOVES THE BOT OR REQUESTS DATA DELETION, ASSOCIATED DATA IS PERMANENTLY REMOVED.



5. DATA SHARING AND THIRD PARTIES
ASHLEY MUSIC BOT DOES NOT SHARE OR DISCLOSE USER DATA WITH ANY THIRD PARTIES.


DATA MAY BE ACCESSED ONLY BY THE BOT OWNER OR AUTHORIZED DEVELOPERS FOR MAINTENANCE PURPOSES.


THE BOT OPERATES ENTIRELY WITHIN THE DISCORD API FRAMEWORK AND FOLLOWS DISCORD’S PRIVACY AND DATA POLICIES.



6. SECURITY
REASONABLE TECHNICAL AND ADMINISTRATIVE MEASURES ARE IMPLEMENTED TO PROTECT STORED DATA AGAINST UNAUTHORIZED ACCESS, LOSS, OR ALTERATION. HOWEVER, NO ONLINE SERVICE CAN GUARANTEE COMPLETE SECURITY, AND USERS ACKNOWLEDGE THIS RISK WHEN USING THE BOT.

7. USER RIGHTS
USERS HAVE THE RIGHT TO:


REQUEST A COPY OF THEIR STORED DATA.


REQUEST DELETION OF THEIR DATA.


WITHDRAW CONSENT BY STOPPING USE OF THE BOT OR REMOVING IT FROM THEIR SERVER.


TO EXERCISE THESE RIGHTS, USERS MAY CONTACT THE BOT OWNER THROUGH THE OFFICIAL SUPPORT SERVER.

8. CHILDREN’S PRIVACY
ASHLEY MUSIC BOT DOES NOT KNOWINGLY COLLECT INFORMATION FROM USERS UNDER THE AGE OF 13. IF SUCH DATA IS IDENTIFIED, IT WILL BE PROMPTLY DELETED.

9. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
THE BOT OWNER RESERVES THE RIGHT TO UPDATE OR MODIFY THIS PRIVACY POLICY AT ANY TIME. USERS WILL BE DEEMED TO HAVE ACCEPTED THE REVISED POLICY IF THEY CONTINUE TO USE THE BOT AFTER CHANGES ARE MADE.

10. CONTACT INFORMATION
FOR QUESTIONS, REQUESTS, OR CONCERNS REGARDING THIS PRIVACY POLICY, PLEASE CONTACT THE BOT OWNER THROUGH THE OFFICIAL SUPPORT SERVER OR DESIGNATED COMMUNICATION CHANNELS.

BY USING ASHLEY MUSIC BOT, YOU ACKNOWLEDGE THAT YOU HAVE READ, UNDERSTOOD, AND AGREED TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY IN FULL.
